               <history>
                    <origin>Written in <origPlace>Iceland</origPlace>, <origDate
                     notBefore="1790" notAfter="1810">c. 1800</origDate>. It appears as if the
                     manuscript consists of three different, yet contemporary, parts. The first part
                     consists of ff. 1-57. This part sets itself apart from the rest by having a
                     more elaborated layout, its use of catchwords and having no pagination. The
                     second part is comprising ff 58-109 and the third partf ff 110-141. As the last
                     part has both a comtemporaneous pagination and a later pagination; it is
                     reasonable to assume that it was an independent part or the first quires of a
                     larger manuscript.</origin>
               </history>
